            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView18"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Preheat the Oven:

Preheat your oven to 425°F (220°C).
Prepare the Potatoes:

Peel and slice the potatoes into 1-inch thick rounds. Pat them dry with a paper towel to remove excess moisture.
Coat Potatoes with Butter and Garlic:

In a bowl, mix melted butter and minced garlic. Dip each potato slice into the butter and garlic mixture, ensuring they are well coated.
Arrange Potatoes in a Baking Dish:

Place the coated potato slices in a single layer in a baking dish.
Season and Add Broth:

Season the potatoes with salt, black pepper, and thyme. Pour the chicken or vegetable broth into the baking dish around the potatoes.
Bake:

Bake in the preheated oven for about 40-45 minutes or until the potatoes are golden brown and fork-tender. Occasionally spoon some of the broth over the potatoes during baking.
Crisp the Tops:

For the last 10-15 minutes of baking, turn the oven to broil to crisp up the tops of the potatoes.
Garnish and Serve:

Remove from the oven, garnish with chopped fresh parsley, and serve the Melting Potatoes immediately while they're hot."
